<subSubSection id="4BC92AA3AD510DD2D811CED3B384418A" pageId="null" pageNumber="160" type="description">
<paragraph id="ED5CAD86A7D07D1A655B01C4A6AE3C26" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">
Die Gattungsmerkmale sind unter den Familienmerkmalen 
<normalizedToken id="B8A947E614BB15D2359D2B13F94F7ADB" originalValue="aufgeführt" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">aufgefuehrt</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96E58B05634E52FA36F7128C56938A67" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="C27C387FE26F6E206E608879206306A7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">
<taxonomicName id="394BF928AAC5211F7B9C09016693966C" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="null" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Selaginella</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="071FA2BF5FB4938CD8BC168EA45125D1" originalValue="umfaβt" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">umfaβt</normalizedToken>
etwa 400 Arten;
</emphasis>
sie 
<emphasis id="14BD166708635587D9DAD1391ECF69DA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">
ist 
<normalizedToken id="C2C35BF76F630DD4812E4F7E81238082" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">ueber</normalizedToken>
die ganze Erde verbreitet
</emphasis>
, die meisten Arten bewohnen aber die 
<emphasis id="5B1740920C918D88F2BAC2BDFAD81073" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">
<normalizedToken id="4ED5691F7A464F99B2198045B7A6A40D" originalValue="äquatorialen" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">aequatorialen</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="49DA7B89DC000728DC419DEC004B1B7E" originalValue="Regenwälder" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">Regenwaelder</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
In 
<taxonomicName id="6057BBE36A05C3593E3DEF7CB588FA10" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
nur 3 Arten, davon 
<taxonomicName id="FE243CDB8ABC5BFC8126D8721FAF02E8" authority="(L.) Link" authorityName="Link" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="null" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="denticulata">
S. 
<emphasis id="CAA78D137FAB4E74A2EE93CC3E4711DE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">denticulata</emphasis>
(
<authorityName id="678F9D4BB160EE8A9ABD49F4DCB55D32" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">L.</authorityName>
) Link
</taxonomicName>
nur im Mediterrangebiet. In Nordamerika neben sexuell normalen auch 
<emphasis id="CBBF757B12BCD32956F48B01B1F6552F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">apomiktische Arten.</emphasis>
Auch unsere beiden Arten sind apomiktisch (Literaturzusammenstellung von Graustein (1930).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF103139E953B32A3A1589D3BAC7271E" pageId="null" pageNumber="160">
<table id="26EBA61A85E57AA4DB24C2C9CED88109" frame="void" pageId="null" pageNumber="160" rules="none" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
